# [Feature Request] Webhook filtering on field changes
created: 2025-01-28, last updated: 2026-03-16, [Read more](https://community.shopify.dev/t/feature-request-webhook-filtering-on-field-changes/6963)

You can do this today with Hookdeck deduplication (I work for Hookdeck).
By setting the dedup key to the variant IDs and their `inventory_quantity`, Hookdeck will only deliver a `products/update` webhook when those quantities change.
Example with a simplified payload:
```
{
"id": 123456789,
"variants": [
{ "id": 111, "inventory_quantity": 10 },
{ "id": 222, "inventory_quantity": 5 }
]
}
```
Config:
```
{
"rules": [
{
"type": "deduplicate",
"window": 86400000, // max 24h
"include_fields": [
"body.variants[*].id",
"body.variants[*].inventory_quantity"
]
}
]
}
```
If Shopify sends another update where only the title or `updated_at` changed, it’s dropped.
When `inventory_quantity` changes, the key changes, and the event is delivered.

